titleStmt.title: Papers of three several conferences, between the Kings most Excellent Majestie, and the Commissioners of Both Kingdomes. Concerning His Majesties comming to the Parliament; and concerning the church and peace of the kingdome: and severall propositions made by His Majestie; and the Commissioners answer. And how the Kings Majestie is come from Newcastle, and lay Wednesday night at Durham, and Thursday night at Bishops Alton: from whence, His Majestie marched Fryday last, on his way towards Holmbie. Perused, and (being ex[a]mined) is appointed to be printed and published, according to Order of Parliament, Feb. 8. 1646.
titleStmt.author: England and Wales. Parliament.
